@startuml
title Bangladeshi Feast - Interaction / Phase Diagram (with Parallel Work)

start

:PHASE 0 (Optional, Day-before)\nMove hilsa to fridge to thaw;
if (Hilsa frozen?) then (yes)
  :Thaw slowly 18â€“24h in fridge;
else (no)
  :Skip thaw phase;
endif

:PHASE 1 (Mise en place)\nGather ingredients + equipment;

fork
  :Soak mustard seeds (15 min);
  :Grind mustard paste + chillies;
fork again
  :Rinse rice;
  :Set rice aside ready to cook;
fork again
  :Peel + chop potatoes;
fork again
  :Chop salad veg (cucumber/tomato/onion);
  :Chill salad bowl (optional);
end fork

:PHASE 2 (Cook base carbs)\nStart rice + potatoes;

fork
  :Cook rice (boil -> simmer -> rest);
fork again
  :Boil potatoes until tender;
  :Drain + steam-dry potatoes;
end fork

:PHASE 3 (Cook main)\nShorshe Ilish;

:Heat mustard oil (to shimmering);
:Temper nigella/panch phoron;
:Add hilsa pieces (light sear optional);
:Add mustard paste + water to gravy;
:Simmer gently until fish just cooked;
:Rest curry off heat (5 min);

:PHASE 4 (Finish sides)\nBhorta + salad;

fork
  :Mash potatoes;
  :Mix with onion + chilli + mustard oil;
fork again
  :Season salad with salt + lemon;
end fork

:PHASE 5 (Plate & serve)\nAssemble full meal;

:Plate rice;
:Top with hilsa + mustard gravy;
:Add aloo bhorta on side;
:Add salad + achar on table;
:Serve mishti doi for dessert;

stop
@enduml
